<div id="bra">
  <h2>Bra Size Measuring Guide</h2>
  <p>Follow the guide lines below on how to find your bra size. Always measure yourself wearing a bra (not
    padded) and take measurements in inches.</p>
  <p>
    <strong>Diagram point 1 - Underbust</strong>
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Place tape measure around you rib cage underneath the bust, hold the tape firmly but not too tight.
    </li>
    <li>If your measurement is an even number then add 4 inches.</li>
    <li>If your measurement is an odd number then add 5 inches.</li>
    <li>This will give you your underbust measurement for your bra size.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    <strong>Diagram point 2 - Overbust</strong>
  </p>
  <p>Place the tape around the fullest part of your bust, do not pull too tight. Note the measurement and
    use the guide below to find your bra size.</p>
  <p>
    <img src="http://jscsecmat.ctscdn.com/content/images/size-guide/bra-size-guide-model.jpg">
  </p>

